               <p>Thomas Johnson was born in<placeName> Wakefield, Yorkshire</placeName>, converted
                  by Methodist preachers in <date when="1748">1748</date>, and became himself a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> in <date when="1752">1752</date>.
                  From <date when="1765">1765</date> he served as one of <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s Assistants, until
                  becoming supernumerary in <date when="1784">1784</date>. Even then he continued to
                  serve into the <date>1790s</date> in a limited assignment. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 220–24; and <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi>
                  (post-Wesley, <date when="1798">1798</date>), 1:414.</p>
            
         
